items.title: BBC Bitesize - What are viruses and malware?
items.htmlTitle: BBC Bitesize - What are viruses and malware?
items.snippet:
Part ofPrimary Computing. Viruses and malware are programs that can attack 
computers, tablets, phones and other digital devices. A virus is a small program 
designed to cause trouble ... By combining the words 'malicious' (meaning '
harmful') and 'software' we get the word 'malware'. Viruses are just one type of 
malware.

items.title: Malware - Simple English Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.htmlTitle: Malware - Simple English Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.snippet:
Malware, short for malicious software, is a kind of software that can be installed 
on a computer without approval from the computer's owner. There are different 
kinds of malware that can hurt computers, such as viruses and Trojan horses. 
The term also includes other intentionally harmful programs, such as spyware 
and ...
